  "texts": [
    "The causal effect of various interventions (e.g., drugs) can be evaluated by manipulating the states of individual nodes and observing the resulting dynamics.",
    "Because Boolean automata can be grouped to model variables with more than two states, the approach is widely applicable for modeling cellular components with various levels of activation, such as the proportion of cells that enter apoptosis in breast cancer cell lines 69.",
    "Indeed, a common application of these models is in studying the effects of combinatorial drug interventions, particularly in the context of cancer 69, 70.",
    "To serve as a component of a digital twin, Boolean networks must reconcile their discrete time steps with physical time.",
    "This is often done by updating node states asynchronously according to tunable node transition rates, essentially treating the dynamics as a continuous Markov process 71."
  ],
